Biography


John R. Baur
Vice President, Eaton Vance Management
Joined Eaton Vance 2005


John Baur is a vice president of Eaton Vance Management, director of global portfolio analysis and portfolio manager on Eaton Vance’s global income team. He is responsible for buy and sell decisions, portfolio construction and risk management for t he firm’s global income strategies. He joined Eaton Vance in 2005.
John began his career in the investment management industry in 2005. Before joining Eaton Vance, he was employed by Applied Materials in an engineering capacity, spending five of his seven years at the firm in Asia.
John earned a B.S. from MIT and an MBA from the Johnson Graduate School of Management at Cornell University.


